Module kivakit.core.resource
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.filesystem

Class Folder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.filesystem.Folder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FileSystemObject, ModificationTimestamped, ResourceFolder, java.lang.Comparable<Folder>
    public class Folder
extends java.lang.Object
implements FileSystemObject, java.lang.Comparable<Folder>, ResourceFolder
    Folder abstraction that extends FileSystemObject and implements the ResourceFolder interface for filesystems. Consumes a FolderService supplied by a filesystem service provider. Filesystem service providers can be found in com.telenav.kivakit.core.filesystem.local (the local filesystem provider) and in the kivakit-filesystems module.

    Factory Methods

    • parse(String) - A folder for the given string
    • of(URI) - A folder for the given URI
    • of(URL) - A folder for the given URL
    • of(java.io.File) - A folder for the given Java file
    • of(Path) - A folder for the given NIO path

    • current() - The current working folder
    • desktop() - The desktop folder
    • userHome() - The user's home folder

    • kivakitTemporaryFolder() - Folder where temporary files can be created
    • kivakitTestFolder(Class) - Folder for test files for the given class

    Operations

    • chmod(PosixFilePermission...) - Changes the access permissions of this folder

    • clearAll() - Removes everything in this folder
    • clearAllAndDelete() - Removes everything in this folder and then deletes it
    • copyTo(Folder, CopyMode, ProgressReporter) - Copies this folder to the given folder
    • copyTo(Folder, CopyMode, Matcher, ProgressReporter) - Copies the matching files in this folder to the given folder
    • delete() - Deletes this folder if it is empty
    • mkdirs() - Creates this folder and any required parent folders
    • renameTo(Folder) - Renames this folder to the given folder
    • ModificationTimestamped.lastModified(Time) - Sets the last modified time of this folder
    • scheduleCleanUpOnExit() - Schedules this folder to be removed when the VM exits

    Checks

    • ensureExists() - Ensures this folder exists or fails
    • exists() - True if this folder exists
    • isFolder() - True if this is a folder and not a file
    • isEmpty() - True if this folder is empty
    • isRemote() - True if this folder is on a remote filesystem
    • isLocal() - True if this folder is on the local filesystem
    • isMaterialized() - True if this folder exists locally
    • isWritable() - True if this folder can be written to
